So this is the red guy.

00:02:15.640 --> 00:02:17.820
He's in pieces all over the place.

00:02:17.820 --> 00:02:21.380
Because your intuition doesn't work well
with speed questions

00:02:21.390 --> 00:02:23.390
and this is why I got a bit surprised about this.

00:02:23.460 --> 00:02:28.000
The first thing to notice is that,
a lot of people think the answer is 30 miles an hour.

00:02:28.140 --> 00:02:33.320
It's really 'sensible' to think about the difference in
speed, which is 30 miles an hour at the start

00:02:33.320 --> 00:02:36.860
and to think, if everything else is the same,
surely that's the speed it's got left over.

00:02:36.860 --> 00:02:40.760
There are lots of reasons why it's not correct,
and one of the reasons you'll probably think is

00:02:40.760 --> 00:02:43.260
I wouldn't be asking this question if it was 30, fine!

00:02:43.420 --> 00:02:45.520
Another intuition thing to ask though, is

00:02:45.520 --> 00:02:48.700
do you think it's slower than 30,
or do you think it's quicker than 30?

00:02:48.700 --> 00:02:50.540
Because if it's not 30, it's one of the two.

00:02:51.120 --> 00:02:53.680
And I'm gonna tell you the answer,
and I'm gonna justify it,

00:02:53.680 --> 00:02:56.220
because when someone told me the answer,
I just bawled. It was...

00:02:57.100 --> 00:03:00.600
I was surprised. I was also a bit shocked
and dare I say it, sobered

00:03:00.600 --> 00:03:03.140
and maybe I changed
my driving habits a little bit, because

00:03:03.140 --> 00:03:05.820
the red guy hits the tree

00:03:05.820 --> 00:03:09.280
assuming all that stuff we assumed, at approximately

00:03:09.480 --> 00:03:11.220
71 miles per hour.

00:03:11.220 --> 00:03:12.840
BRADY: Seventy-one!
BEN: Seventy-one.

00:03:12.840 --> 00:03:16.860
He has not even reached the speed
that the blue guy started braking at

00:03:16.860 --> 00:03:18.460
and he's hit the tree at that speed.

00:03:18.460 --> 00:03:21.960
There's the difference between
not crashing at all, well done blue guy

00:03:21.960 --> 00:03:25.580
and hitting a brick wall, or a tree in this case,
at 71 miles an hour.

00:03:25.920 --> 00:03:29.920
And that was from a difference of 30 miles an hour
to start with, and everything else is the same.

00:03:29.920 --> 00:03:32.100
It's pretty easy to justify this, but

00:03:32.100 --> 00:03:33.880
the answer is sobering enough.

00:03:33.880 --> 00:03:36.020
So I think we should justify it before I leave you

00:03:36.020 --> 00:03:39.260
to go and change your driving habits,
and myself on my way home.

